-----------------------------------------------------------
    Triggers
-----------------------------------------------------------
CREATE TRIGGER name when event ON tablename action
	- when E {BEFORE, AFTER}
	- event E {DELETE, INSERT, UPDATE}
	- action E {FOR EACH ROW BEGIN .. END, FOR EACH STATEMENT BEGIN .. END, WHEN expression BEGIN .. END}
	- OLD and NEW are special references
- triggers should be more or less supported by all DBMS

-----------------------------------------------------------
     Stored procedures
-----------------------------------------------------------
- very DBMS specific
- can reduce system info I/O
- increase security by granting access only to stored procedures
	- can't touch data directly


